# Adding PCEA Prescription Functionality

## Overview
Added the ability to prescribe PCEA directly from the AutoPrescribe frontend, integrating seamlessly alongside the existing PCA and Painless Labor features.

## Changes Made
- **Network Analysis:** Analyzed the `pcea.pcapng` network capture to identify PCEA-specific parameters for `IpoC11GSave`.
- **Backend ([his_client.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py))**: 
  - Updated [prescribe_package](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py#81-246) to support the `PCEA` package mode.
  - Set Fentanyl dose to `0.5` mg and Route to `PCE`.
  - Set Frequency to `ASORDER`.
  - Set drug control code mapping to `ANES_TEST2`.
  - Excluded Ropivacaine per user instruction.
- **Frontend ([templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/templates/index.html))**: 
  - Added a new `🟣 Prescribe PCEA` button.

## Validation Strategy
- Python syntax successfully validated.
- **Manual User Review**: Please launch the application (`python app.py`) and perform a test PCEA prescription to ensure the HIS API successfully processes the payload and generates the `Controlled_Drug_Sheet_P022.pdf`.
